  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '-- Building Placer --

    This menu is placed in the top left corner
    and you can select which item you wanna buy (road, bus stop, traffic light and
    vehicles). When the game has started by default the mouse is selected. When an
    item is selected the price of the item is displayed and when you click on the
    map it is placed down (vehicles can only be placed on roads) and the price is
    subtracted from your account balance. If you want to sell any item you purchased
    select mouse and press shift (toggles demolish mode on/off) this activates demolish
    mode and by clicking on the object you sell it and the value is added to your
    balance.


    -- Data Display --

    When a facility, traffic light, city or
    vehicle is clicked (Bulding Placer must have mouse selected) a display appears
    with the data of the object that was selected.

    - interactions -

    <SELL>

    The
    object disappears from the landscape and the worth of this item is added to your
    account balance

    <(-) / (+)>

    Adds/Subtracts a second from the length
    of this traffic light''s green light''s length

    <REPAIR>

    Makes this
    vehicle''s condition the best it can be for the "Repair cost" price

    <SET
    ROUTE>

    Enters this vehicle''s Set Route mode. In this mode by clicking on
    icons above buildings you define a path for the vehicle (the order matters in
    which you click them). Route can be "Reset", saved with "OK" or discarded with
    "Cancel". Invalid moves will be shown through error messages.

    - Object types
    -

    <FACILITY>

    ID: Identification of object

    Traffic: How frequently
    the facility is visited

    Consume: What does the facility need

    Produce:
    What does the facility make

    <CITY>

    ID: Identification of object

    Satisfaction:
    Resource stocks of the city depending on the "Needs"

    Needs: The list of
    resources missing

    <TRAFFIC LIGHT>

    ID: Identification of object

    Worth:
    The value of the traffic light

    Green light(s): Seconds until the light changes
    to red

    Buttons: <SELL>

    <VEHICLE>

    ID: Identification of object

    Resource:
    What does the vehicle carry

    Capacity: How much the vehicle can carry

    Condition:
    How used is this vehicle (if too much vehicle disappears)

    Repair cost: How
    much it costs to repair the vehicle

    Worth: The value of the vehicle

    Buttons:
    <SET ROUTE>, <REPAIR>, <SELL>


    -- Minimap --

    In the top right corner
    you can find the minimap. The arrow in the middle points the direction where
    you are looking at the landscape.


    -- Menu Bar --

    In the bottom left
    corner there is your account balance. In the middle you can find the time manager
    (Pause, Play, Forward, Fast Forward). In the bottom right corner you can see
    the in-game time.


    -- Help Menu --

    You can access this exact menu from
    the "Game Menu" during gameplay'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
